ENTRY       EC 4.1.3.43                 Enzyme
NAME        4-hydroxy-2-oxohexanoate aldolase;
            BphI
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-carbon lyases;
            Oxo-acid-lyases
SYSNAME     (S)-4-hydroxy-2-oxohexanoate pyruvate-lyase (propanal-forming)
REACTION    (S)-4-hydroxy-2-oxohexanoate = propanal + pyruvate
ALL_REAC    (other) R05298
SUBSTRATE   (S)-4-hydroxy-2-oxohexanoate
PRODUCT     propanal [CPD:C00479];
            pyruvate [CPD:C00022]
COMMENT     Requires Mn2+ for maximal activity [1,2]. The enzymes from the bacteria Burkholderia xenovorans and Thermus thermophilus also perform the reaction of EC 4.1.3.39, 4-hydroxy-2-oxovalerate aldolase [1,2,6]. The enzyme forms a bifunctional complex with EC 1.2.1.87, propanal dehydrogenase (CoA-propanoylating), with a tight channel connecting the two subunits [3,4,6].
